# 🕷️ Website Scraper with Python & Pandas

A modular and extensible Python-based web scraping tool that extracts data from websites and stores it in structured formats using `pandas`. Ideal for scraping tabular data, product listings, or public data for analysis.

---

## 📂 Project Structure

website_scraper/
│
├── main.py # Entry point to run the scraper
├── config.py # Configurations like headers/user-agent
├── requirements.txt # Project dependencies
│
├── scrapers/ # Scraping logic lives here
│ └── generic_scraper.py # A basic table scraper using pandas
│
├── utils/ # Reusable functions like saving data
│ └── data_handler.py
│
├── data/ # Scraped data output
│ └── scraped_data.csv
│
└── logs/ # Logs (optional)
└── scrape.log

yaml
Copy
Edit

---

## 🚀 Features

- Scrape HTML tables using `pandas.read_html`
- Save scraped data to CSV
- Modular architecture to add custom scrapers
- Easily configurable headers / user-agent
- Clean separation of logic and utilities

---

## 🔧 Setup

1. **Clone the repo**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/website_scraper.git
   cd website_scraper
Install dependencies

